revision.text:
[[Image:Town crier Alan Myatt, Hitchin, UK.jpg|thumb|right|Alan Myatt in [[Hitchin]] in [[Hertfordshire]] in 2009]] '''Alan Myatt''' (born 1957) is a [[town crier]] who set two Guinness World Records. As well as being the loudest crier, recording a cry of 112.8 decibels,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/health/1396836.stm|title=Quiet night's sleep for 'world's loudest man'|work=BBC News|accessdate=18 August 2011|date=19 June 2001}}</ref><ref>[http://www.thetimes.co.uk/tto/news/uk/article3763184.ece 'No tears as town crier receives medal for long service' - [[The Times]] - 13 May 2013]</ref> he also set the [[Guinness world record]] for vocal endurance, issuing a one-hundred word proclamation every 15 minutes for a period of 48 hours.<ref name=Citizen>{{cite web|url=http://www.gloucestercitizen.co.uk/Oyez-Oyez-Town-crier-Alan-Myatt-rings-25-years/story-18938044-detail/story.html|title=Oyez! ' Oyez! Town crier Alan Myatt rings in 25 years of service|publisher=[[Gloucester Citizen]]|accessdate=2014-04-14|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140414163321/http://www.gloucestercitizen.co.uk/Oyez-Oyez-Town-crier-Alan-Myatt-rings-25-years/story-18938044-detail/story.html|archivedate=2014-04-14|df=}}</ref> He is a crier to commerce, industry and heritage, and can be seen at exhibitions, promotions and trade fairs across Europe. He is also a [[toastmaster]], [[master of ceremonies]] and themed character actor.<ref name=Citizen/><ref>[http://www.thememan.co.uk/ Alan Myatt's official website]</ref>
He is the official town crier for the [[Gloucester|City of Gloucester]],<ref name=Citizen/> for [[Letchworth|Letchworth Garden City]]<ref>[http://www.thecomet.net/news/dickensian_market_returns_to_letchworth_1_3085790 'Dickensian market returns to Letchworth' - The Comet - 7 December 2013]</ref> and [[Hitchin]] in [[Hertfordshire]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hawkinsofhitchin.co.uk/history.htm |title=George Hawkins History |accessdate=18 August 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120205205900/http://www.hawkinsofhitchin.co.uk/history.htm |archivedate=5 February 2012 |df= }}</ref> for London's [[Covent Garden]]<ref>[http://www.coventgardentrust.org.uk/rentceremony/ Myatt and the Covent Garden Area Trust Rent Ceremony]</ref> and also for various venues in the capital including the [[Camden Market#Stables Market|Stables Market]] in [[Camden Town]].<ref name=Citizen/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.coventgardenlondonuk.com/events-entertainment-culture/articles/paying-the-rent-again |title=Paying the Rent Again |accessdate=18 August 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111005231213/http://www.coventgardenlondonuk.com/events-entertainment-culture/articles/paying-the-rent-again |archivedate=5 October 2011 |df= }}</ref>
In July 2015 he crossed the [[English Channel]] to France in an attempt to be the first British town crier since 1066 to make an announcement on the French side of the water.<ref>[http://www.westerndailypress.co.uk/Town-crier-cross-Channel/story-27510184-detail/story.html#ixzz3qAAI3FDa 'Town crier Alan Myatt of Gloucester to cross Channel' - [[Western Daily Press]] - 30 July 2015]{{Dead link|date=October 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>
Myatt is a member of the Ancient and Honourable Guild of Town Criers.<ref>[http://www.ahgtc.org.uk/towns/ Myatt on the Ancient and Honourable Guild of Town Criers website]</ref>
