{{About||the former English footballer|Eric Arnold (footballer)}}
'''Eric Arnold''' is an [[United States|American]] [[journalist]] and [[author]], formerly a news editor of ''[[Wine Spectator]]'' and [[wine]] and [[spirits]] writer and lifestyle editor for ''[[Forbes|Forbes.com]]''.<ref name=dec>Shaw, Lucy, ''Decanter.com'' (September 30, 2009). [http://www.decanter.com/news/news.php?id=290046 First Big Crush to be made into a film]</ref> In 2010, Arnold joined the online wine community enterprise [[Bottlenotes]] as Editorial Director.<ref>''The New York Times'' (June 5, 2010). [https://www.nytimes.com/2010/06/06/fashion/weddings/06TUSHINGHAM.html Weddings: Carly Tushingham, Eric Arnold]</ref> Arnold has previously worked as a [[stand-up comedian]].<ref>Cooper, Michael, ''New Zealand Listener'' (April/May, 2008). [http://www.listener.co.nz/issue/3546/columnists/10948/down_to_earth.html Down to earth]</ref>
In September 2007, Arnold published ''First Big Crush'', an account of a year spent immersed in the [[New Zealand wine|wine culture of New Zealand]].<ref>Colman, Tyler, drvino.com (October 11, 2007). [http://www.drvino.com/2007/10/11/first-big-crush-qa-with-eric-arnold/ First Big Crush: Q&A with Eric Arnold]</ref><ref>McGill, Christy, vinography.com (April 5, 2008). [http://www.vinography.com/archives/2008/04/book_review_my_first_big_crush.html Book Review: First Big Crush by Eric Arnold]</ref><ref>Wark, Tom, fermentation.com (October 01, 2007). [http://fermentation.typepad.com/fermentation/2007/10/first-big-crush.html "First Big Crush"...Not Your Father's Wine Book]</ref><ref>goodgrape.com (September 17, 2007). [http://goodgrape.com/index.php/articles/comments/youthful_wine_spectator_editor_releases_first_book/ Irreverent Wine Spectator Editor Releases First Book]</ref> In September 2009, a team of New Zealand filmmakers headed by Ben Ruffell announced intentions to adapt the book into a feature film.<ref name=dec/> ==See also== *[[List of wine personalities]]
