atrick.htm|title=Mason Patrick|publisher=Arlington Cemetery.net|accessdate=2010-03-22}}</ref>}} {{mem/a2 |first=John J. <!--- Also listed in "Spanish-American War and Philippine Insurrection combatants" and "Pancho Villa Expedition combatants" ---> |last=Pershing |year=1886 |nota=[[General of the Armies]]; [[Spanish–American War]]; [[Philippine–American War]]; [[Moro Rebellion]]; commander of 8th Regiment in the [[Pancho Villa Expedition]]; led the [[American Expeditionary Force]] in [[World War I]] |ref=<ref name="blackjack">{{cite book|last=Vandiver|first=Frank E. |title=Black Jack: The Life and Times of John J. Pershing – Volume I |publisher=Texas A&M University Press| location=College Station, TX|year=1977|edition=3|page=67|isbn= 0-89096-024-0}}</ref>}} {{mem/a2 |first=Charles S. |last=Farnsworth |year=1887 |nota=[[Major general (United States)|Major General]]; [[Spanish–American War]], [[Philippine–American War]]; [[Battle of Saint-Mihiel]]; commander of the [[37th Infantry Division (United States)|37th Infantry Division]]; founder of [[Fort William McKinley]]; founder and commandant of the [[United States Army Infantry School]]; the [[Gen. Charles S. Farnsworth County Park]] in [[Altadena, California]] is named for him |ref=<ref name="farnsworth">{{cite web|url=http://www.bobbygrich.org/Afghanistan%20Era/History/48th_inf_bde_cbt_place_holder_pa.htm|title=48th Infantry Brigade Combat Team|publisher=48th Infantry Brigade Combat Team Place Holder Page|accessdate=2010-03-22|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110725085720/http://www.bobbygrich.org/Afghanistan%20Era/History/48th_inf_bde_cbt_place_holder_pa.htm|archivedate=25 July 2011|df=dmy-all}}</ref>}} {{mem/a2 |first=Robert Lee |last=Howze |year=1888 |nota=[[Major general (United States)|Major General]]; [[American Indian Wars]], [[Spanish–American War]], [[Philippine–American War]]; [[Meuse-Argonne Offensive]]; commander of the [[1st Cavalry Division (United States)|1st Cavalry Division]]; com