isRaulEsteves/Luis_Raul_Esteves.htm|title=Major General Luis Raúl Esteves Völckers|date=1 November 2002|publisher=Bell South|accessdate=2010-03-22|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100127022626/http://bellsouthpwp.net/r/u/ruiz_b/LuisRaulEsteves/luis_raul_esteves.htm|archivedate=27 January 2010|df=dmy-all}}</ref>}} {{mem/a2 |first=Thomas B. <!--- Also listed in "World War II" ---> |last=Larkin |year=1915 |nota=[[Lieutenant general (United States)|Lieutenant General]]; reconnaissance officer during [[Second Battle of the Marne]]; [[Tunisia Campaign]] in [[World War II]]; Quartermaster General (1946–1949) |ref=<ref name="larkin">{{cite web|url=http://www.arlingtoncemetery.net/tblarkin.htm|title=Thomas B. Larkin|publisher=Arlington Cemetery.net|accessdate=2010-03-22}}</ref>}} {{mem/a2 |first=Dwight |last=Johns |year=1916 |nota=[[Brigadier general (United States)|Brigadier General]]; [[Pancho Villa Expedition]], [[World War II]]; recipient of the [[Distinguished Service Medal (U.S. Army)|Army Distinguished Service Medal]] |ref=<ref name="johns">{{cite web|url=http://digital-library.usma.edu/libmedia/archives/cullum/VOLUME_6B_cullum.pdf |title=Biographical Register of the Officers and Graduates of the U.S. Military Academy |publisher=United States Military Academy |accessdate=2010-04-24 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100531131358/http://digital-library.usma.edu/libmedia/archives/cullum/VOLUME_6B_cullum.pdf |archivedate=31 May 2010 |df= }}</ref>}} {{mem/a2 |first=Hugh John <!--- Also listed in "Engineers" and "World War II" ---> |last=Casey |year=1918 |nota=[[Major general (United States)|Major General]]; instructor and engineer company commander during [[World War I]]; Chief Engineer for General of the Army [[Douglas MacArthur]] for the [[South West Pacific theatre of World War II]]; initial designer of [[The Pentagon]]; father of Major [[Hugh Boyd Casey]]; father-in-law of Major General [[Frank Butner Clay]] |ref=<ref name="casey">{{cite web|url=http://www.arlingtoncemetery.net/hjcasey.htm|title=Hugh John Casey|publisher=Arlington Cemetery.net|accessdate=2010-03-22}}</ref>}} {{mem/a2 |first=William M. |last=Miley |year=1918 |nota=[[Major general (United States)|Major General]]; [[World War II]]; commander of the [[503rd Infantry Regiment (United States)|503rd Parachute Infantry Regiment]]; commander of the [[17th Airborne Division (United States)|17th Airborne Division]] and [[11th Airborne Division (United States)|11th Airborne Division]]; recipient of the [[Silver Star]] and two [[Distinguished Service Medal (U.S. Army)|Army Distinguished Service Medals]] |ref=<ref name="miley">{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1997/09/28/us/william-miley-99-a-paratroop-pioneer-dies.html?pagewanted=1|title=William M. Miley obituary|work=The New York Times|accessdate=2010-04-25 |date=28 September 1997}}</ref>}} }}
