'''Operation Cannonball''' is an [[United States|American]] [[Central Intelligence Agency]] operation that was disclosed in 2008.<ref name='NY Times Qaeda Cannonball'>{{cite news | first=Mark | last=Mazetti |author2=Dave Rodhe | title=Amid Policy Disputes, Qaeda Grows in Pakistan | date=2008-06-30 | publisher=New York Times | url =https://www.nytimes.com/2008/06/30/washington/30tribal.html |  accessdate = 2008-06-30  }}</ref> Beginning in 2006, it was intended as part of an effort to capture [[Osama Bin Laden]] and eliminate [[Al Qaeda]] forces in [[Pakistan]].<ref name='NY Times Qaeda Cannonball' />  There was reportedly "mounting frustration" among [[The Pentagon|Pentagon]] officials due to the ongoing delay and deployment of special forces units, as originally planned in the Cannonball program.<ref name='Reuters Cannonball June 30 08'>{{cite news | title=Secret US military plan for Pakistan on hold-report | date=2008-06-30 | publisher=Reuters | url =https://www.reuters.com/article/featuredCrisis/idUSN29326556 | accessdate = 2008-06-30 }}</ref> The operation was reportedly hampered by conflicts between CIA offices, leading to large delays in the deployment of the program.<ref name='NY Times Qaeda Cannonball' /> Partially to blame for the presently failed deployment of the program was conflict among United States intelligence agencies, along with resources having been diverted to the [[War In Iraq]].<ref name='Reuters Cannonball June 30 08' />

The existence of the covert program, and its various internal conflicts, was revealed to the public by ''[[The New York Times]]'' on June 30, 2008.<ref name='Canada FP NY Times Cannonball'>{{cite news | first=Judi | last=McLeod | title=New York Times again exposes “highly classified Pentagon order” | date=2008-06-30 | publisher=Canada Free Press | url =http://www.canadafreepress.com/index.php/article/3724 | accessdate = 2008-06-30}}</ref> ''The New York Times'' article was said to be "exposing highly classified Pentagon orders".<ref name='Canada FP NY Times Cannonball' />

