'''Philip Cabaud''' is a wine maker in [[Houston, Texas]],  United States, who's hired a winemaker who has won high marks  [http://cabaudwines.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/Robert-Parker-reviews.pdf high marks] from well-known [[wine]] reviewer, [[Robert M. Parker, Jr.|Robert Parker]], after just a few short years in the business. After a career in the insurance industry, Philip and his wife, Bonnie Cabaud <ref name="The Napa Wine Project: Cabaud Wines">[http://www.napawineproject.com/cabaud-wines/]</ref> invested significantly  in a new venture: a [[winery]], [http://cabaudwines.com/ Cabaud Wines], in 2009. As newcomers to the world of wine making, they sought the insights of Luc Morlet,<ref name="Is Luc Morlet the Future of High-End California">[http://dobianchi.com/2015/02/25/morlet-family-vineyards/]</ref> a well known winemaker who has guided vintages for several well-known labels ranging from the Peter Michael Winery to the Staglin Family Vineyard. Their efforts won them prominence in the NorCal wine blog".  

